The GoomWave project is an attempt to make a versatile, hackable, and simple LED library for GameCube controller modders looking to make cool LED animations.

Materials/Supplies list:

Note: I have not checked every single link especially the Amazon ones for quality products. They are just demos/pictures of approximately what you want

Project-specific supplies:
DotStar (APA102 LEDs) - https://www.adafruit.com/product/2343
5050 Breakout Board - https://www.adafruit.com/product/1762
Arduino Nano + programming cable - https://www.amazon.com/XCSOURCE-ATmega328P-Controller-Arduino-TE359/dp/B015MGHH6Q/ref=sr_1_8?keywords=arduino+nano+5v&qid=1556622153&s=electronics&sr=1-8
JST 3 Position connector Female- https://www.digikey.com/product-detail/en/jst-sales-america-inc/B3B-XH-A-LF-SN/455-2248-ND/1651046
JST 3 Position connector Male - https://www.digikey.com/product-detail/en/jst-sales-america-inc/03JQ-BT/455-2966-ND/5875089
Flexible Protoboard - https://www.adafruit.com/product/3904
30 AWG wire wrap wire (Get 5 different colors for wire management) - https://www.amazon.com/Yootop-Solder-Wrapping-Tin-Plated-N-30-1000/dp/B07GLBS9ZB/ref=sr_1_1?keywords=30awg+wire+wrap+wire&qid=1556622730&s=electronics&sr=1-1
